    "content": "nullExperience Cloud\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Experience Cloud\n Understand the Basics\n Plan & Prepare\n Set Up & Configure\n Manage Users and Data Access\n Build & Customize\n Create Use-Case Driven Sites\n Secure Your Site\n Test & Deploy\n Manage & Moderate\n Managers, Moderators, and Admins Working Together\n Experience Cloud Site Moderation Strategies and Tools\n Organize Experience Cloud Sites with Topics\n Customize Recommendations in Experience Cloud Sites\n Gamification\n Recognition Badges\n Recognition Badges Limitations\n Recognition Badges Setup\n Missions\n Assign Recognition Badges to Experience Cloud Site Members\n Delete Assigned Badges\n Use the API to Give Recognition Badges Sample Code\n Reputation Overview\n Share a Link to Your Experience Cloud Site\n Switch Between Your Salesforce Org and Your Experience Cloud Sites\n Use Reporting in Experience Cloud Sites\n Considerations\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nEXPERIENCE CLOUD\nAssign Recognition Badges to Experience Cloud Site Members\n\nAssigning badges to members helps reward them for staying engaged in the Experience Cloud site.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Professional, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\nUSER PERMISSIONS NEEDED\nTo assign recognition badges:\tAssign Recognition Badges in Experience Builder Sites\nOpen the member’s profile page.\nClick either the Give Badge button at the top of the profile or the Give button on the Recognition Badges card.\nChoose which badge you want to assign by clicking Change badge.\nAdd a message letting the member know why they’re getting the badge, and click Give.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
